<xsl:stylesheet xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform" xmlns:dita="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" xmlns:comm="http://www.lexis-nexis.com/glp/comm" xmlns:docinfo="http://www.lexis-nexis.com/glp/docinfo" version="2.0" exclude-result-prefixes="dita comm docinfo">

	<dita:topic xmlns="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="psl_landingpgs-body">
  <title>Body <lnpid>id-UK13-30008</lnpid></title>
  <body>
    <p><sourcexml>comm:body</sourcexml> becomes <targetxml>/seclaw:seclaw/seclaw:body</targetxml></p>
    <p>All source documents can be identified as belonging to this stream by checking the
        <sourcexml>docinfo:selector</sourcexml> content. If and only if the content of element
        <sourcexml>docinfo:selector</sourcexml>
      <b><u>starts</u></b> with the exact text "LandingPages_" (including the underscore) but also
      does not contain the exact text "LandingPages_TopicTree" then the document belongs to this
      stream and should be converted according to the instructions provided in this document.
      Otherwise, the document is not a landing page document and these instructions should not be
      used.</p>
    <note>Previously this document provided instructions for two distinct types of source
      documents: <b><u>POD documents</u></b> and <b><u>Topic Tree documents</u></b>. However, topic
      tree documents are no longer converted using the instructions in this document. Please see the separate subsections <xref href="pods.dita"/> and <xref href="topic_trees.dita"/> for more details.</note> 
    <p>Instructions given within this <b><u>Body</u></b> section will always explicitly specify the particular source XPaths whose children should be converted according to the instructions in the section <xref href="general.dita"/>. If the instructions for a source XPath do not explicitly specify that the section <xref href="general.dita"/> should be used, then it should not be used.</p>    
    <section>
      <title>Source XML </title>
      <codeblock>

&lt;COMMENTARYDOC ...&gt;
  &lt;docinfo ...&gt;
    &lt;!--...--&gt;
    &lt;docinfo:selector&gt;LandingPages_Precedents&lt;/docinfo:selector&gt;
    &lt;!--...--&gt;
  &lt;/docinfo&gt;
  &lt;comm:body&gt;
    &lt;!--...--&gt;
  &lt;/comm:body&gt;
&lt;/COMMENTARYDOC&gt;

      </codeblock>
    </section>
      <section>
        <title>Target XML </title>
        <codeblock>

&lt;seclaw:seclaw ...&gt;
  &lt;seclaw:head/&gt;
  &lt;seclaw:body&gt;
    &lt;!--...--&gt;
  &lt;/seclaw:body&gt;
  &lt;doc:metadata&gt;
    &lt;!--...--&gt;
    &lt;classify:classification classscheme="selector"&gt;
      &lt;classify:classitem&gt;
        &lt;classify:classitem-identifier&gt;
          &lt;classify:classname&gt;LandingPages_Precedents&lt;/classify:classname&gt;
        &lt;/classify:classitem-identifier&gt;
      &lt;/classify:classitem&gt;
    &lt;/classify:classification&gt;    
    &lt;!--...--&gt;
  &lt;/doc:metadata&gt;
&lt;/seclaw:seclaw&gt;

        </codeblock>
      </section>
    <section>
      <title>Changes</title>
      <p>2016-07-12: <ph id="change_20160712_JCG">Modified instructions in this topic to indicate that topic trees should no longer be converted using the instructions in this document.</ph></p>
      <p>2015-03-07: <ph id="change_20150307_JCG">Modified wording, including adding instructions regarding a new method for identifying all landing page documents by checking the start of <sourcexml>docinfo:selector</sourcexml> content.</ph></p>
    </section>
